############################
# Arduino based variometer #
############################

Features :
---------
- High precision altitude with improved ms5611 code
- High precision vertical velocity with InvenSense accelerometer (optionnal)
- Screen display with waveshare e-paper 1,54 inch : altitude, vertical speed, ground speed, glide ratio and more (optionnal)
- Ground speed and glide ratio with GPS device (optionnal)
- Flight tracking with SD card reader and GPS (optionnal)
- Bluetooth communication with external device (optionnal)
- Battery level (optionnal)
- Microcontroler Cortex M0+


How to build :
--------------
Pre-build kits can be found here :


Contact me for more informations at prunkdump@gmail.com


Variometer Wiring :
-------------------

See schematic.pdf for full diagram.

ms5611/mpu9250 board :
CJMCU-117 MPU9250+MS5611 circuit interface
SDA -> Arduino D11 - SDA
SCL -> Arduino D12 - SCL
VCC -> Battery RAW +
GND -> GND

Speaker (simple) :
Speaker + -> 120 Ohms resistor -> Arduino A3
Speaker - -> Arduino A4

Speaker (amplified with L9110) :
L9110 IA -> Arduino A3
L9110 IB -> Arduino A4
L9110 OA -> Speaker +
L9110 OB -> Speaker -
L9110 VCC -> Battery RAW +
L9110 GND -> GND

Waveshare e-paper 1.54 inch board :
SCLK -> Arduino D9 / SCK
DIN/MOSI -> Arduino D8 / MOSI
DC -> any Arduino pin (default D7)
CS -> any Arduino pin (default D1)
RST -> any Arduino pin (default D2)
BUSY -> any Arduino pin (default D3)
VCC -> Arduino VCC - 3.3V
GND -> GND

GPS board :
GPS TX pin -> D5 serialNmea  Pin 5 
GPS RX pin -> TX Serial1     Pin 14 (only used for GPS configuration)
GPS VCC -> Battery RAW +
GPS GND -> GND

Bluetooth module :
Bluetooth RX pin -> D4 serialNmea   Pin 4 
Bluetooth TX pin -> RX Serial1      Pin 13  
Bluetooth VCC -> Battery RAW +
Bluetooth GND -> GND

Push Button Left A1
Push Button Right A2 
Push Button Center A5  --- ON/OFF

Detection USB   A6
Alim Manager    D6
Reset command   D0 


Code configuration :
--------------------

!!! Don't skip this step !!!
Open ./libraries/VarioSettings/VarioSettings.h and check all the parameters.
To "comment" a line put a "//" at the beginning.
Edit, modify parameters and copy SETTINGS.TXT to SDCARD

---------------------------------
YOU CAN NOW TRY YOUR VARIOMETER !
---------------------------------